pro.taskana.impl.report

Class Report<Item extends QueryItem,ColumnHeader extends ReportColumnHeader<? super Item>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • pro.taskana.impl.report.Report<Item,ColumnHeader>
  • Type Parameters:
    Item - QueryItem whose value is relevant for this report.
    ColumnHeader - ReportColumnHeader which can determine if an <Item> belongs into that column or not.
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CategoryReport, ClassificationReport, CustomFieldValueReport, DetailedClassificationReport, TaskStatusReport, WorkbasketLevelReport

    public abstract class Report<Item extends QueryItem,ColumnHeader extends ReportColumnHeader<? super Item>>
extends Object
    A Report represents a an abstract table that consists of ReportRows and a list of <ColumnHeader>s. Since a report does not specify <Item> and <ColumnHeader> it does not contain functional logic. Due to readability implicit definition of functional logic is prevented and thus prevent initialization of an abstract Report. In order to create a specific Report a subclass has to be created.
